text: Let the blind man give you his perspectives. I’ve upgraded well, my brother calls it a downgrade. From the 13 promax to the 13 mini. And here’s why. Whenever I would use the braille keyboard, the phone would slip and fall right out of my hands and onto the floor. And it was incredibly hard to hold. But with the 13 mini, now the Apple company slapping us right in the face because they are saying that they will not make the 14 mini for us blind users and I find that pretty disrespectful. Because with this, I can use it with one hand, I can grip the phone easy. I can just carry the energizer battery pack right on me, and I go from 50 to 90, in 20 minutes. When I upgrade phones, I won’t be able to do that probably. This is a perfect size for me, it’s like having a miniature iPod touch with cellular service
